First, what is a Collector?
👉 A Collector is used at the end of a stream to collect the processed data
into a final form.
📌 collect() is the terminal operation
📌 Collectors is a utility class that provides ready-made collectors
1️⃣ Collectors.toList()
📌 Converts stream into a List
2️⃣ Collectors.toSet()
📌 Converts stream into a Set (removes duplicates)
3️⃣ Collectors.toMap()
📌 Converts stream into a Map (key → value)
Map<Integer, String> map =
    list.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.toMap(
            s -> s.getId(),     // key
            s -> s.getName()    // value
        ));
⚠️ Important: Keys must be unique, otherwise exception occurs.
🧠 Interview Tip:
If duplicate keys → provide merge function
4️⃣ Collectors.counting()
📌 Counts elements in stream
5️⃣ Collectors.summingInt()
📌 Sums values
int totalMarks =students.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.summingInt(Student::getMarks));
Related:
->summingLong()
->summingDouble()
7️⃣ Collectors.maxBy() / minBy()
📌 Find max or min element
Optional<Student> topper =
    students.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.maxBy(
            Comparator.comparing(Student::getMarks)
        ));
🧠 Returns Optional → may be empty
8️⃣ Collectors.groupingBy()
📌 Groups elements by a property
Map<String, List<Student>> groupByDept =
    students.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(Student::getDepartment));

🧠 Real-life:
Students grouped by department
Employees grouped by role
Orders grouped by status
With counting:
Map<String, Long> countByDept =
    students.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(
            Student::getDepartment,
            Collectors.counting()
));
9️⃣ Collectors.partitioningBy()
📌 Splits into two groups only (true / false)
Map<Boolean, List<Student>> result =
    students.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.partitioningBy(
            s -> s.getMarks() > 60
));

🔟 Collectors.joining()
📌 Joins strings
String names =
    list.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.joining(", "));

Result:
Ram, Shyam, Mohan
With prefix & suffix:
Collectors.joining(", ", "[", "]");